name: Joseph Skewes
tweet: Consider someone who wants to build a DApp or buy a digital asset secured by a smart contract, will they trust their smart contract / assets to a small consortium of hand picked #IOTA nodes, who could collude & act against their interest? Or would they opt to use #Ethereum..

name: Joseph Skewes
tweet: #IOTA took a different approach with their smart contracts.  Smart contracts were created in a layer on top of the feeless, distributed ledger.   https://t.co/1nV6MxpFd2  What does this mean? Not every IOTA node enforces smart contract txns as they do on #Ethereum.

name: Joseph Skewes
tweet: This is where fees on #Ethereum come from, network participants bidding over each other for inclusion in this (relatively) slow distributed ledger, because the miners have an economic incentive to execute txns based on the fees (gas price) offered by those who want in.
